👩🏼‍🍳 🍞SO PROUD OF THIS SEEDED SANDWICH BREAD I MADE! Tag me in your 🥪 if you make it: 

Seeded Sandwich Bread
* 500 g all purpose flour
* 1 + 1/2 tsp (10 grams) fine salt
* 1/2 cup (35 grams) sunflower seeds
* 2 tbs sesame seeds
* 2 tbs psyllium husk
* 340 mls warm water
* 2 tsp honey
* 1 + 1/2 teaspoons active dry yeast
* 4 tbs (55 grams) soft unsalted butter
* For topping: 1 beaten egg, sesame seeds

Mix the honey into the warm water then add the yeast. Wait 10 min for the yeast to activate & get foamy. Add the liquid to the dry ingredients & mix to a dough. Let it rest for 10 min. Mix in the butter in small portions until all incorporated. Cover the dough with a towel & let it double in size— about 90 min- 2 hours. TIP: Put the bowl in the warm oven & it will rise faster! Roll it out into a rectangle using a rolling pin then roll it up into a very tight log. Place the log in a greased loaf pan to double in size— about 1 hour. Brush on the beaten egg & sprinkle with more sesame seeds. Bake in your pre-heated oven at 400 degrees F for 35-40 min. Let the bread cool for at least 2 hours so you can slice it to make a yummy Sammy!  #homebaker #homebaking #breadmaking #baking #bakingfromscratch #bread #baker #bakersofinstagram #yum #madefromscratch #bsbakery

Cherry filling:

- 1/4 cup (28g) cornstarch
